{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πυρρός</b>, ά <br /> (<i>Ionic dialect</i> ή), όν, but Trag. and <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>πυρσός</b>, ή (<i>Doric dialect</i> ά), όν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 32, “HF” 361 (Lyric poetry), 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus 2.70, conjecture in 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 316 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pelopidas” 22 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: (πῦρ):— <b>flame-coloured, yellowish-red</b> (πυρρὸν ξανθοῦ τε καὶ φαιοῦ κράσει γίγνεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 68c, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1054b13, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 9.600), ᾠοῦ τὸ π\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. the <b>yolk</b> of an egg, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “γυναικεῖα” 2.171, “PLit.Lond.” 170 (1st c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ λευκότης γίγνεται πυρρή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 20;\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] of sediment in urine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Epid.” 6.1.5. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially of persons <b>with red hair</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Xenophanes Poeta Philosophus 16.2, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.108; π. τὸ Σκυθικὸν γένος 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 20; οἱ ἁλιεῖς π. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 966b26; π. τρίχες [prev. author] “GA” 785a19 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; of the colour of the first beard, γενειάς A.[same place]; γένυες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [θρίξ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.130, compare 6.3. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> generally, <b>tawny</b>, λέων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “HF” [same place], 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 785b17, “Anthologia Graeca” 6.263 (1st c.AD: Leonidas Alexandrinus Epigrammaticus); βοῦς “PLond.” 3.890.5, 10 (1st c.BC, written πυραί), 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.363b; ἵππος NT.Rev.6.4; [πώλου] ἡ χρόα στίλβουσα τῆς χαίτης πυρσότατον 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pelopidas” 22; αἶγες “PHib.” 1.120.6 (3rd c.BC)\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ χρώματα τῶν κυνῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 4.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> of more positive colour, <b>red</b>, χλανίς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.139; ῥόδον 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus 2.70; ἕψημα LXX.Gen.25.30 \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π. <b>redness</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 329:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —_Epic dialect_ _comparative_ (for πυρρότερα), πῠρώτερα φοινίσσεσθαι to be of a <b>brighter</b> red, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 798. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>blushing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 900 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also κύων.. πύρσ᾽ ἔχουσα δέργματα glaring with <b>bloodshot</b> eyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1265. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>paroxytone</i> Πύρρος, ὁ, “Pyrrhus”, as <i>proper name</i>; also Πύρϝος, name of a horse, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 3119h50 (from Corinth);compare Πυρϝίας “IG” 4.492.5 (Mycenae, 6th c.BC), Πυρϝαλίων [prev. work]517.4 (from Argos). (Prob. from *πυρσϝός.) \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4450","accentedUnicode":"πυρρός","relatedNos":